text: Fahrenzhausen is a municipality located on the river Amper in the district of Freising in Bavaria in Germany. The town is about 30 Kilometers north of Munich. ==Geography== Fahrenzhausen has several villages in its community: Appercha, Bachenhausen, Bergfeld, Grosseisenbach, Grossn√∂bach, Jarzt, Kammerberg, Lauterbach, Unterbruck, Viehbach and Weng. == Literature == * Hans Schertl, "Kirchen und Kapellen im Dachauer Land (German)" ==References== Category:Freising (district)
